								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">Et surrexi nocte ego, et viri pauci mecum, et non indicavi cuiquam quid Deus dedisset in corde meo ut facerem in Jerusalem: et jumentum non erat mecum, nisi animal cui sedebam.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">And I arose in the night, I and some few men with me, and I told not any man what God had put in my heart to do in Jerusalem, and there was no beast with me, but the beast that I rode upon.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">When I stirred abroad, it was at dead of night, with only a few men to attend me, and none mounted but myself.</div></div></td>
